    <h2>Hello, Nihao and Marhaban</h2>
    <p>I'm Haomiao, a M.S. Candidate in Information Systems and Applied Information Sciences (with a concentration in Connective Media) at <a class="inline-link" href="https://tech.cornell.edu/">Cornell Tech</a> at Cornell University. At Cornell, I am advised by <a class="inline-link" href="https://people.jacobs.cornell.edu/mor/">Prof. Mor Naaman</a> and <a class="inline-link" href="https://nixdell.com/">Prof. Nicola Dell</a> on my ongoing reserach project centering on misinformation, recommendation systems and social media platforms.</p> 
    <p>Prior to Cornell, I graduated from the College of Arts and Science, <a class="inline-link" href="https://www.nyu.edu/">New York University (NYU)</a> with a B.A. degree in Computer Science and in Middle Eastern Studies.</p>
    <p>Currently I am interested in creating all sorts of programs for social good, designing user-friendly interfaces, and creating data analyses and visualizations. For Summer 2020, I will be heading to Amazon Web Services as a Software Development Engineer intern.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="../assets/HaomiaoHanResume.pdf" class="inline-link">here</a> to download my resume. Feel free to visit my <a class="inline-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/haomiaohan/">LinkedIn</a> and <a class="inline-link" href="https://github.com/haomiaohan">GitHub</a> pages as well.</p>
